    "The findings revealed that when subjected to a small pulse (0.9 V), the memorization gradually diminished over one day.",
    "Conversely, an application of a larger pulse (2 V) resulted in sustained memorization, effectively transitioning from STM to LTM.",
    "This ability to memorize multiple patterns and the selectivity observed in CBA devices holds crucial role for weight storage in neural networks.",
